\fs10 \f0 \fs25 \f0 \pard \s6 \posx1934 \posy3314 \phpg \pvpg \absh-6833 \absw7350 \dxfrtext200 \qj \li50 \fi441 \ri71 \sl-260 \tx50 \tx491 \tqr \tx7278 Like cassettes, disk drives serve two principal purposes: they are a medium on which commercial software can be made available to your computer; and they also allow you to save, more or less permanently, programs or other data which you've created yourself However, they offer far better performance than a cassette drive. At somewhat less than $300, the disk drive represents a relatively serious investment, but it is so much faster and more reliable than a cassette unit that it is worth the price for most users.\par 
\fs10 \f0 \fs25 \f0 \pard \s7 \posx1934 \posy3314 \phpg \pvpg \absh-6833 \absw7350 \dxfrtext200 \qj \li58 \fi441 \ri58 \sl-260 \tx58 \tx499 \tqr \tx7291 It is possible to use old\_style Commodore drives, which were built for use with the Commodore 64, with the new Commodore 128. The most popular drive built by Commodore for the C64 was the 1541, a single drive unit (meaning it would hold only one disk at a time). Dual\_drive units are also available from other manufacturers. All of these units will also work on the Commodore 128. However, they do not take full advantage of one of the major improvements of the Commodore 128 over the Com\-modorq 64: the increased speed of the disk drives.\par 
\fs10 \f0 \fs25 \f0 \pard \s8 \posx1934 \posy3314 \phpg \pvpg \absh-6833 \absw7350 \dxfrtext200 \qj \li50 \fi441 \ri50 \sl-261 \tx50 \tx491 \tqr \tx7299 For the C128, Commodore has announced an entirely new line of disk drives. The single drive model is the 1571, shown in Figure 2\_3. This drive operates in three modes, corresponding to the three personalities of the Commodore 128 computer. In C64 mode, it's completely compatible with the old 1541 drive, and runs at the same speed as the old drive. In C128 mode, it runs five times faster; and in CP/M mode, it runs faster still \'97and is also compatible with most existing CP/M formats. The dual\-drive version of the drive is called the 1572.\par 
}\pard \sl-261 \tx50 \tx491 \tqr \tx7299 \fs24 \f0 {\pard \posx1930 \posy10444 \phpg \pvpg \absh-2301 \absw7357 \dxfrtext200 \fs10 \f0 \fs31 \f2 \i \pard \s9 \posx1930 \posy10444 \phpg \pvpg \absh-2301 \absw7357 \dxfrtext200 \li70 \ri4418 \sl-319 \tx70 \tqr \tx2938 Data liansfer Speed\par 
